afterOrderExecution(bytes32,((address,ad.details: This is the callback called by GMX after every order execution. We implement the callback in order to track "claimable collateral" at the moment it is created, because otherwise it is not possible to calculate it purely on-chain. For decrease orders, we track the claimable collateral amount if the negative threshold of the price impact was exceeded We handle only decrease orders types (MarketDecrease, StopLossDecrease, LimitDecrease, Liquidation). If new order types are added in the future, this function might need to be updated.

getManagedAssets().details: There are 5 ways that positive value can be contributed to this position 1. Collateral in the GMX positions, taking into account price impact and profit/loss 2. Pending orders: deposited collateral in market increase orders, plus execution fees of all orders 3. Assets held by the External Position. Those assets are monitored via the trackedAssets variable 4. Collateral that eventually can be claimed from GMX positions where collateral was freed up from decreased positions. 5. Funding fees that can be claimed from the GMX protocol

params._market: The address of the market to check.

returns.isCallbackContractSet_: A boolean value indicating if the callback contract is set for the specified market.

init(bytes).details: Nothing to initialize for this contract

params._actionData: Encoded data to execute the action

getClaimableCollateralKeyToClaimableColl.notice: Retrieves the claimable collateral key token

getDebtAssets().notice: Retrieves the debt assets (negative value) of the external position

getManagedAssets().notice: Retrieves the managed assets (positive value) of the external position

getMarketToIsCallbackContractSet(address.notice: Retrieves the status of whether the callback contract is set for a given market.

receiveCallFromVault(bytes).notice: Receives and executes a call from the Vault
